		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_0" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P>Chapter 9 Part 2:</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Well, it's always a pleasure to meet new people." Ruby smiled, reaching across the table to shake the duo's hands. "How long have the three of you known each other?"</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Since way back." Harold declared.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Since were were toddlers, basically." Will filled in.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Well, the two of us knew each other since we were weeks old - we met Plue a bit later." Harold expanded upon the previous statements.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"How interesting." Ruby said.&nbsp;</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"We didn't think that Plue would join up." Harold confessed, and Will nodded.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Our friend may be many things, but a fighter she is not."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Is that so?" Ruby grinned as she drank from a cup of something. "You should see her and Kraken train."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Oh?" Two heads turned towards Kraken, who inwardly groaned.&nbsp;</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Yeah." He admitted. "She's quite a quick learner. My arms hurt after every sparring session - she's pretty good with a sword."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Well, who would have known?" Harold exclaimed in glee, shoving Plue on the shoulder gently. "If that's the case, how good do you think she'll be at the end of the year?"</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Good enough to survive on the battlefield for longer than a few seconds, and that's what matters." Kraken declared.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Seems fair." Harold nodded, before turning back to Ruby. "Tell me, is your friend always so macabre?"</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"I'm afraid so." Ruby admitted. "Kraken here seems to suffer from a chronic lack of a sense of humour."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Shame, that." Harold sighed. "Everyone should have a sense of humour, I don't see how you can get through life without one."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>Kraken shrugged. "I manage."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"I'm sure you do, my friend." Harold declared. "But still... it must be kind of gloomy, right?"</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Perhaps." Kraken admitted. "But when you haven't experienced anything else, how can you make an accurate comparison?"</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"You speak the tragic truth. Well don't worry!" Harold raised his hand into the air with a flourish. "By the end of the year, I guarantee you'll have a tangible sense of humour."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"No thank you." Kraken deadpanned. "I'm perfectly fine."</P>
                
            
			
				<div style="width:98%; max-height:100px; overflow:hidden;" class="UserSignature lia-message-signature">
	The Maelstrom Minifigure, Knight Of The Old Speech, Time Lord.<BR /><BR />"Somebody once told me that knowledge is a sharper weapon than a sword. Before I charge into a fight, I could use a little more of that." - Toa Lesovikk.
</div>
			
			
