		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_7" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P>Ahem...</P><P>The circular part on the katana between the blade and hilt is called the hand-guard.&nbsp; I would get into more specifics if I could.&nbsp; Also, while it doesn't curve that much it would make hidding it in a staff extremely difficult.&nbsp; Escrima sticks would be more easily concealed.</P><P>FYI from a martial artist...</P>
                
            
			
