		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_11" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P>&nbsp;Chapter 9 Part 3:</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"That's what they all say." Harold shrugged. "In any case, are the rest of you excited for tomorrow's prowess trials? I can't wait to see the skills the combatants have to offer!"</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"I'm interested too - if only to see whether Intrepid can live up to his claims." Kraken muttered, sipping on a coffee.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"So, does anyone know what the test entails?" Will input.&nbsp;</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"i belive it's SOMETHING related to combat, but aside from that... I'm afraid I don't know." Ruby admitted.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Anyone else?" Will scanned the table, only to recieve shakes of the head from Kraken, Harold and Plue.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Afraid I don't know either." A voice declared, and the group at the table turned around to see Joy and Walaby standing behind them.&nbsp;</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Mind if we join you?" Walaby grinned.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Make yourselves at home." Ruby declared before Kraken could object, and the Assembly pair took their places at the table.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"So what faction is everyone here in, anyway?" Harold asked. "I don't intend to discriminate, I'm just wondering."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Our dorm are in Sentinel." Ruby filled in, indicating to Kraken and Plue.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"The two of us are in Assembly." Joy said in regards to herself and Walaby.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Venture League." Will said.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Sentinel." Harold declared. "The action-y stuff is for me, though I don't know how good I am..."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Don't undersell yourself." Will grinned. "You're good at the tactics stuff and you're handy with a sword, and that's all you really need."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"How good at the tactics stuff?" Kraken interjected.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"I've never beaten him at chess. Or risk." Will revealed. "Or monopoly."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Well, how many times have you played?" A grinning Kraken asked. "What if you've only played once?"</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"I see what you did there." Joy shot a glance towards Kraken.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"No, we actually play very frequently." Harold said. "Plue's our witness - she'd want to do something else and I'd just be repeatedly creaming the two of them."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"Y-yeah, that happened a lot." Plue said.</P>
                
            
			
				<div style="width:98%; max-height:100px; overflow:hidden;" class="UserSignature lia-message-signature">
	The Maelstrom Minifigure, Knight Of The Old Speech, Time Lord.<BR /><BR />"Somebody once told me that knowledge is a sharper weapon than a sword. Before I charge into a fight, I could use a little more of that." - Toa Lesovikk.
