s="emoticon emoticon-thinking" id="thinking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/thinking.png" alt="Thinking" title="Thinking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I thought katanas at least had that little disk thing in place of it.<img class="emoticon emoticon-thinking" id="thinking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/thinking.png" alt="Thinking" title="Thinking" /> I suppose then it could blend in with the staff right off, though, so there wouldn't be a need to disguise it. But then you have the curvature&nbsp;of the blade to deal with.<img class="emoticon emoticon-confused" id="confused" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/confused.png" alt="Confused" title="Confused" /> I'm not sure how much katanas curve though, so maybe it wouldn't even be a problem.<img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Yeah, that's true... but I didn't really think about that as a cross guard for some reason.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>I suppose the staff's cross guards could appear like Kylo Ren's on his lightsaber. <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Heehee, yeah.<img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Do they flick out at the side, as metal bits part of the mechanism, or are they composed of energy and turn on with the blade?</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>They're composed of the energy like from the blade. <img class="emoticon emoticon-nerd" id="nerd" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/nerd.png" alt="Nerd" title="Nerd" /> <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P>
                
            
			
