		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_13" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Rock_Raider_fan_no1 wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Haroldosaur wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Samlooploop wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Rock_Raider_fan_no1 wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Samlooploop wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Rock_Raider_fan_no1 wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Samlooploop wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />TALKINGCARL1000 wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Samlooploop wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Rock_Raider_fan_no1 wrote:<BR /><BLOCKQUOTE><HR />Haroldosaur wrote:<BR /><P>Chapter 8 Part 3:</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"A staff, of all weapons?" Plue queried. "Seems pretty uninteresting."</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>"That's why I like it." Intrepid explained. "A staff is both unassuming and versatile..."</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>You know, a staff could be modified to have energy or electrical output for a higher versatility. <img class="emoticon emoticon-thinking" id="thinking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/thinking.png" alt="Thinking" title="Thinking" /> Although, that addition may make it unassuming... <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I want one that detaches into escrima sticks.<img class="emoticon emoticon-cool" id="cool" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/cool.png" alt="Cool" title="Cool" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I would want a staff that is made of a hidden sword, but the sword is concealed in the wood.</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>That would be neat!<img class="emoticon emoticon-happy" id="happy" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/happy.png" alt="Happy" title="Happy" /> I wonder how one would design the cross guard for&nbsp;that. Maybe make it&nbsp;retractable.<img class="emoticon emoticon-thinking" id="thinking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/thinking.png" alt="Thinking" title="Thinking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Do you&nbsp;<EM>need</EM> a cross guard? Katanas don't have them. <img class="emoticon emoticon-thinking" id="thinking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/thinking.png" alt="Thinking" title="Thinking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I thought katanas at least had that little disk thing in place of it.<img class="emoticon emoticon-thinking" id="thinking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/thinking.png" alt="Thinking" title="Thinking" /> I suppose then it could blend in with the staff right off, though, so there wouldn't be a need to disguise it. But then you have the curvature&nbsp;of the blade to deal with.<img class="emoticon emoticon-confused" id="confused" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/confused.png" alt="Confused" title="Confused" /> I'm not sure how much katanas curve though, so maybe it wouldn't even be a problem.<img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Yeah, that's true... but I didn't really think about that as a cross guard for some reason.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>I suppose the staff's cross guards could appear like Kylo Ren's on his lightsaber. <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Heehee, yeah.<img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Do they flick out at the side, as metal bits part of the mechanism, or are they composed of energy and turn on with the blade?</P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>They're composed of the energy like from the blade. <img class="emoticon emoticon-nerd" id="nerd" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/nerd.png" alt="Nerd" title="Nerd" /> <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I guess it should be composed of the same stuff as the blade... but wouldn't it be cool to have a cane that mechanically turned into a sword complete with crossgaurd? <img class="emoticon emoticon-happy" id="happy" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/happy.png" alt="Happy" title="Happy" /> <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /></P>
                
            
			
